HEADWORD: Turanians
<hw>Tu*ra"ni*ans</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An extensive division of mankind
including the Mongols and allied races of Asia, together with the Malays
and Polynesians.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A group of races or tribes
inhabiting Asia and closely related to the Mongols.</def>⟦br⟧
